# Companion Conversation
# A travelling companion the player can talk to at any time. Multiple
# topics, each looping back to a main menu so the player can ask about
# other things or leave.
#
# The hub-and-spoke shape is the canonical pattern for party members,
# guildmasters, and any NPC you keep returning to.

NPC: companion

Companion:
What is on your mind?

Player:
How are you holding up?
=> Wellbeing

Player:
Got any stories?
=> Story

Player:
We should keep moving.

Scene: Wellbeing
Companion:
Tired. But I have been worse. Do not worry about me.

Player:
Take a rest sometime.
=> Main Menu

Player:
Soldier on, then.
=> Main Menu

Scene: Story
Companion:
There was this one time, before all this, when I worked the harbour at Drystone Bay.

Player:
Tell me more.
=> Story Continued

Player:
Maybe later.
=> Main Menu

Scene: Story Continued
Companion:
A merchant ship caught fire just as it docked. Three sailors made it off. I pulled the fourth out of the water. Heaviest thing I have ever carried.
=> Main Menu

Scene: Main Menu
Companion:
Anything else?

Player:
How are you holding up?
=> Wellbeing

Player:
Got any stories?
=> Story

Player:
No, that is all.
